Class ExtensionManager

java.lang.Object
  be.abeel.io.ExtensionManager

public class ExtensionManager
extends java.lang.Object

File extension manager, makes sure a file has an specified extension, or one that is commonly used for that type of file.

Author:
Thomas Abeel

extension

public static java.lang.String extension(java.lang.String fileName,
                                         java.util.List<java.lang.String> exts)
Makes sure a file has the specified extension, or one of the specified compatible ones.

Parameters:
fileName - The input file name
exts - a Listwith the allowed extensions. The first one will be used to add if the original file name doesn't have a compatible extension.
Returns:
a new file name with the correct extension

extension

public static java.lang.String extension(java.lang.String fileName,
                                         java.lang.String corExt)
Adds the correct extension to a file. If the file already has an other extension, the new one will just be concatenated to it if they don't match.

Parameters:
fileName - input file name
corExt - a string with the correct extension
Returns:
the new file name with the correct extension

extension

public static java.io.File extension(java.io.File file,
                                     java.lang.String corExt)
Adds the correct extension to a file. If the file already has another extension, the new one will be appended. If the file already has the correct extension, it will be left alone.

Parameters:
file - name of input file
corExt - the target extension
Returns:
a new File name with the correct extension

extension

Adds the correct extension to a file. If the file already has an other extension, the new one will just be concatenated to it if they don't match.

Parameters:
file - input file name
exts - a list of allowed extensions, the first one will be used to add.
Returns:
the new File with the correct extension
